,Recommended,229600,1096036,"Posted: 24 March, 2013",all,Pyyhkari,"First, move the mouse pointer away from the ""Add to cart"" link.Now, go take a look at the ""game"" community here on Steam.You'll notice how many people truly and deeply hate the ""game"".I hear there's a web browser demo of the game on the creators' website - go check that out.There are no goals in this game - or none explicitly stated. When I played this, I was very sleepy (in my case, that's comparable to being tipsy or drunk). I didn't find another players, but I spent time talking with the simulated partner at the house. I selected lines I had seen rise from the waves, creating a discussion made of platitudes, sweet nothings and such, but affixing it a meaning by myself.When I quit the game, I was very surprised to notice that I had spent 50 minutes in the game. I... existed.I bought this game in a sale. The asking price without a sale is, in my opinion, too high. I don't know how I'll like the game when I play it again when I'm wide awake. I don't know if I'll ever end up playing the game with a real person rather than a computer simulation. But for now, I can't say that I personally truly regret spending 2.5€ on this ""game"" - for a game it is not but something else. But you might still find that to be too high a price."
